paragraphs.text: every generation blames the one before and all of their frustrations come beating on your door
i know that i'm a prisoner to all my father held so dear i know that i'm a hostage to all his hopes & fears i just wish i could have told him in the living years
whoa crumpled bits of paper filled with imperfect thoughts stilted conversations i'm afraid that's all we've got
